        "title_line1": "Best Friends,",
        "title_line2": "Bound by Craft.",
        "body": "K&A began the way most quiet houses do — between two people who saw the same picture before either said it aloud. Karishma and Ashita built this atelier on a simple conviction: that a bride's clothing should be made with intention, considered stitch by stitch, rather than assembled off a rack. What started as an instinct between friends is now a Mumbai atelier, where every lehenga, every corset, every draped silhouette begins as a private conversation — long before it becomes a garment.",
