        "title_line1": "Nothing Here",
        "title_line2": "Is Machine-Made.",
        "body": "Zardozi worked thread by thread. Sequins placed one at a time. Boning shaped and stitched until a corset holds a bride the way she wants to be held for twelve hours, not twelve minutes. Every K&A piece moves through the same hands, from first sketch to final fitting — because a garment this considered cannot be rushed, and should never be duplicated.",
        "credit": "The same hands have, on occasion, dressed private clients across film and fashion — among them actress Palak Tiwari, styled in one of our hand-cut corset drape sarees.",
